==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remord
<hw>Re*mord"</hw> <pr>(r?-m?rd")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>remordere</ets> to bite again, to torment: cf. F.
<ets>remordre</ets>. See <er>Remorse</er>.]</ety> <def>To excite to
remorse; to rebuke.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Skelton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remord</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Remord
<hw>Re*mord"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To feel remorse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Elyot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remordency</ent>⟦br⟧
